<div type="definition">

    <p resp="#CH" modified="2020-10-17T22:38:52.205+09:00">LOVE SOMETHING INTENSELY AND INTENSELY NEED IT.  </p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>[ARCHAIC/CURRENT]</p>
<p>[[FREQUENT/RARE]]</p>
<p>[HIGH-DEGREE/LOW-DEGREE]</p>
<p>[POETIC/PROSAIC]</p>
<p>1. The most general word for a strong and permanent liking for alcohol and the like is dān 耽 / 酖 / 湛.</p>
<p>[HIGH-DEGREE], [POETIC]</p>
<p>2. Miǎn 湎 is an elevated poetic word for addiction, typically to wine.</p>
<p>[ARCHAIC], [POETIC]</p>
<p>3. Chén 沈 is occasionally used to refer to a person being excessively prone to vices of any kind including wine and women.</p>
<p>[GENERAL], [HIGH-DEGREE]; [[RARE]]</p>
<p>4. Xù 酗 is a rare archaic word referring to addiction to wine as expressed in action.</p>
<p>[ARCHAIC], [POETIC]; [[RARE]]</p>
<p>5. Yòng 醟 is a very rare word referring to excessive fondness of wine.</p>
<p>[[RARE]]</p>
        </div>
